?num=37533">Susanoe Orbatos</A> - <A HREF="http://zs.20m.com/">Zenith Sage</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaauminki.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aauminki</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will KICK YOUR @$$</span><br>  Posts: 463<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 2:39:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=525.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Big Faction Hits</span><hr size=1> No nameds are really <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> big</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> hits that warrant you using time to kill them, much better off tagging along with arena groups and just owning a lot of stuff for faction imo. I think all the zeks are the same +CoV hit in Kael, so just sit around the city square and see invis line and pull to there worked for me. About 16 hours of factioning in non-optimal groups got me from max kos to dubious.<br><br>Don't kill rif giants though, it's a waste of time <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p><big><center><b><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=25220>Veteran S. Bbastage</a><br><i><a href=http://companions.windsofstorm.net>The Companions</a></i> <br>Warlizard on Tribunal</big><br><a href=mailto:remmer@mail1.stofanet.dk>Send an email</a><br><small><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=5798>Aauminki Starlure (oom)</a></b></small> <br><i>preference to persons who sign up in advance and show up on time</i></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaerildroigheann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeril Droigheann</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/con's RED</span><br>  Posts: 359<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 12:25:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=525.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Big Faction Hits</span><hr size=1> Generally, Vind is 1 faction level and Statue is 2 when you get out of super KOS.  Tormax gives NO positive CoV faction at all, just Dain and Yelinak. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45589">Aeryl Firebrand</a>, Warlord<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=65788">Aeril Droigheann</a>, 59 Preserver, Semi-Retired<br><a href="http://berglad.stormloader.com/">Undaunted</a>, Xegony<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usplaktar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Splaktar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 1:16:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=525.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Big Faction Hits</span><hr size=1> Fastest way is sitting in arena killing Prot Zeks, named Priests of Vallon/Tallon, and Kallis, etc.... 6 hours or so should get you back to Dubious, prolly another 12-18 hours to get ally.... CoV sux. <p><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=55265">Splack 60 High Priest</a><BR><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=55273">Gurgel 60 Warlord</a><BR><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=55268">Samas 54 Heretic</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/unogagim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nogagim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/8/02 5:46:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=525.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Big Faction Hits</span><hr size=1> How much of a role does CHA play in the size of your faction hits? I hear 2nd hand information from people in groups that the higher the CHA, the bigger the faction hits. I was wondering if anyone has some information regarding this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubrutultarewmarr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brutul Tarew Marr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 234<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/9/02 12:44:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=525.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.blackcompany.cc/member_pics/45.jpg height=185 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Big Faction Hits</span><hr size=1> The statue is a big  hit.  I tagged along leeching faction off of one vindi/statue raid with my CoV monk and went from apprehensive to kindly.  I know from experience that you can do all the arena giants and Vindi once and not lose ally with max zek faction, but the statue is THE big CoV hit.  As someone else said, Tormax doesn't give any +CoV faction.  It might take you 3 or 4 statue hits to get you out of scowls, but after that a couple will get you back to ally. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6629>Brutul Vilesilencer</a><br>Barbarian Warlord of the <a href=http://www.blackcompany.cc>Black Company</a><br>Tarew Marr</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showPrevMessage?topicID=525.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showNextMessage?topicID=525.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=525.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.emailToFriend?topicID=525.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.threadControl?topicID=525.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=525.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=525.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"><